column1: #Text=Somali parliament rejects president 's dismissal of prime minister
#Text=Somalia 's parliament overwhelmingly voted Monday to keep Nur Hassan Hussein as their prime minister , blocking President
#Text=Abdullahi Yusuf Ahmed 's attempt at dismissing the prime minister and his " corrupt , inefficient " government .

column1: #Text=President Yusuf announced his motion to dismiss Hussein on Sunday , saying his government was " unable to perform its duties " in matters such as dealing with the Islamic militants who have taken over most of the country .
#Text=The latest dispute between the two involved efforts to reconcile with the Alliance for the Re-liberation of Somalia ( ARS ) , the country 's main opposition group .
#Text=The UN -sponsored peace process has been decried by Yusuf as dealing with terrorists .

#Text=Hussein countered that the president had no authority to strip the prime minister of his post , and that the transitional federal charter required the approval of parliament for such an action .
#Text=" The president was speaking in his usual personal capacity , contrary to the rules and regulations , " Hussein said prior to the special parliamentary session in Baidoa .

#Text=Despite Yusuf 's hope that the parliament would endorse his decision , members of parliament were strongly supportive of Hussein 's government , with 143 members recognizing the government 's legitimacy , 20 rejecting its legitimacy and 7 abstaining .
#Text=" Therefore the government of Hassan Hussein is legitimate , " said Aden Mohamed Nur , the parliamentary speaker .

#Text=Hussein , whom Yusuf appointed little more than a year ago after the resignation of Ali Mohamed Gedi , had previously survived a vote of no confidence in September , when he faced accusations of embezzling state funds .

#Text=The only obstacle in front of my government was the president ,  Hussein told members of parliament after the vote , " and since I have the confidence of the MPs I hope it will be effective henceforth .

column1: #Text=" Yusuf had no immediate comment on the vote , but he had previously stated he would comply with parliament 's decision if they chose to block his dismissal .

#Text=Yusuf has blamed the prime minister for the instability plaguing the politically fragile state , while Hussein has accused the president of trying to  sabotage " peace efforts between the transitional government and the ARS .

column1: #Text=Fighting between the Islamic opposition and Somali-backed troops from Ethiopia , the African Union , and the UN has killed thousands of Somalis and displaced millions .

#Text=Jean Ping , chairman of the African Union Commission , said the dispute within the transitional government has the potential of undermining efforts for " further reconciliation , peace , and stability in Somalia .
